{
  "texts": [
    "Let t elapsed be the time elapsed since the task began, and t max be the maximum allowable time.",
    "The safety condition is:t elapsed ≤ t max.The validation function V time (a) is:V time (a) = I(t elapsed ≤ t max).",
    "G. Problem FormulationThe primary goal of this framework is to enable service robots to operate safely and efficiently in dynamic and unseen environments.",
    "To achieve this, the robot's task planning and execution are formalized as a sequence of discrete actions A = {a 1, a 2,..., a n }, where each action a i contributes to the successful completion of the task while adhering to safety constraints.The robot operates within an environment E, which includes an array of objects O = {o 1, o 2,..., o m }.",
    "Each object o i is characterized by spatial coordinates (x i, y i), physical attributes P = {p 1, p 2,..., p k }, and dynamic properties such as temperature and stability."
  ]
}